The paper focuses on the relation classification component of a slot filling system, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper proposes type-aware convolutional neural networks, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves information retrieval techniques, which could place it under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with named entity recognition, which is a sub-topic of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
